Package: bitToken2
Type: Package
Title: Tokenization and Analysis of Text Data
Version: 0.2.1
Author: SHIN Jong-Hwa
Maintainer: SHIN Jong-Hwa <sens5900r@modernity.or.kr>
Description: Provides functions for tokenizing and analyzing text data. The main function bitToken() tokenizes a character vector or a list of character vectors and returns a data frame with the frequency count of each token. The function bitToken_info() calculates summary statistics of the number of tokens in a character vector or a list of character vectors. The function bitToken_check() checks if a specified column in a data frame contains only text data and is suitable for tokenization with bitToken().
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.2
Imports:
    dplyr,
    rlang,
    stringr
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)

